<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1325,1540,1886]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
COMMENTS: Bürgers' New 
<collectingCountry box="[587,671,1540,1566]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Guinea</collectingCountry>
specimens all went directly to the Zoological Museum in Berlin (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gebhardt, L." box="[423,646,1580,1606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref14150" refString="Gebhardt, L. (1964) Die Ornithologen Mitteleuropas - ein Nachschlagewerk. Bruhlscher Verlag, Giessen, 404 pp." type="book" year="1964">Gebhardt 1964: 57</bibRefCitation>
), whence Lord Rothschild must have received the female 
<typeStatus box="[264,367,1620,1646]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">holotype</typeStatus>
used in the original description. He referred to additional female specimens, which makes the 
<specimenCount box="[471,602,1660,1686]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
specimens now remaining in Berlin arguable 
<typeStatus box="[1149,1265,1660,1686]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">paratypes</typeStatus>
. The 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature &amp; London, XXIX" box="[264,412,1700,1726]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref14729" refString="ICZN International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, XXIX, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999</bibRefCitation>
: article 32.5.2.1.) demands the deletion of German 'Umlauts', so that today the epithet is spelled 
<emphasis box="[482,593,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">buergersi</emphasis>
. These specimens were not mentioned in Meise's MS. The 
<typeStatus box="[264,366,1780,1806]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">holotype</typeStatus>
is AMNH 678693 (female, 
<date box="[729,899,1780,1806]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1913-06-11">11 June 1913</date>
, Schraderberg, Coll.: Bürgers, no. 2064), this being the only specimen of the taxon from Bürgers' collection received by that institution.
</paragraph>
